# cargo-fuzz build output (recreated by every `cargo fuzz run`).
target/

# Crash reproducers written by libfuzzer when a target panics or
# trips a sanitizer. These are local-investigation artefacts, not
# part of the regression suite — once minimised they get promoted
# into `corpus/<target>/` (which IS committed) or, if appropriate,
# pinned by a unit-test fixture in the parent crate.
artifacts/

# Coverage data from `cargo fuzz coverage` runs.
coverage/

# Note: `corpus/<target>/` directories are NOT ignored. The seed
# corpus is committed so each fresh `cargo fuzz run` starts from a
# known-good baseline (and so CI, when wired up, exercises the same
# inputs every contributor sees locally).
